article.headline: North Texas 72, Louisiana-Monroe 40
article.story: EDs: North Texas 72, Louisiana-Monroe 40. MONROE, La. (AP) -- Quincy Williams scored 17 points to lead four North Texas players in double figures as the Mean Green crushed Louisiana-Monroe, 72-40, on Wednesday in a Sun Belt Conference matchup. North Texas (17-9, 8-7) held Louisiana-Monroe to a season-low 13 points in the opening period and the Warhawks (10-17, 4-11) hit just 28.3 percent of their shots. Louisiana-Monroe finished the game with 16 turnovers and 13 field goals made. Still, the undersized Warhawks kept the game close through the first part of the opening period and, with just under 10 minutes remaining, trailed by four at 13-9. But then, Louisiana-Monroe suffered a drought on offense that lasted until the end of the period and saw the Mean Green string together a 23-3 run to end the half. North Texas lead at intermission, 34-13. In the second half, North Texas outscored the Warhawks by 11 en route to the 32-point victory. Raphelle Turner came off the bench to score a team-high eight points for Louisiana-Monroe. He also had eight rebounds.
